        </custodhist>
        <scopecontent id="ref8">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>These papers deal mostly with schools in the 1800's. Box I contains photographs, North District bills and records books, and miscellaneous papers from Hoyden Hill School. Box II contains records books, workbooks, tests and town flyers. Boxes III and IV contain text books.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <bioghist id="ref9">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>The Lacey's in this collection were from Plattsville in the northeast corner of Fairfield. They were involved in education and politics.</p>
        </bioghist>
